Description: Fragment of neck and shoulder of East Greek pottery large vessel, perhaps a krater; cream slip on neck at least on interior and on exterior; interior reserved; exterior: trace of decoration on neck; band at turn to shoulder; frieze of pendent lotus buds and flowers with worn added red on shoulder.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.1060)
